      },
      {
        "decision": "Middleware runs before all authenticated routes",
        "implementation_note": "Extract the API key from the authentication layer, then invoke the rate limit check. If the key is not yet authenticated, rate limiting does not apply (or apply a separate unauthenticated limit if needed — out of scope for now)."
      },
      {
        "decision": "Retry-After header must reflect actual wait time, not a fixed value",
        "implementation_note": "With sorted sets, Retry-After = timestamp of the oldest entry in the set (ZRANGE key 0 0) + 60 - now. This gives the exact number of seconds until the oldest request expires and a slot opens. Round up to the nearest integer."
      },
      {
        "decision": "Fail-open on Redis failure",
